---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Combination Insurance | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="Layer life, critical illness, and disability coverage into one integrated protection plan. Independent insurance advice from Heidi Blondin Financial in Kingston, Ontario."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Insurance</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Combination Insurance</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        No single type of insurance covers every risk. A combination approach layers life, critical illness, and disability coverage to create a protection plan without gaps.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Why layering coverage matters</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>Think about the main threats to your family's financial security: you die, you're seriously ill and can't work for a time, or you're disabled and can't work long-term. Each scenario is different — and each requires a different type of coverage to address it properly.</p>
        <p>A combination insurance policy — or a coordinated package of individual policies — ensures you're covered for all three. Some insurers offer a single combined product; others make it more efficient to hold complementary individual policies together. We help you design the right mix for your situation and budget.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-plum flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-white">L</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-1">Life Insurance</h3>
              <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Pays a lump sum to your beneficiaries if you die. Covers mortgages, debts, income replacement, and final expenses so your family doesn't have to.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-plum flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-white">CI</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-1">Critical Illness Insurance</h3>
              <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Pays a tax-free lump sum if you're diagnosed with a serious illness (cancer, heart attack, stroke, and more). You're alive — but your finances need support while you recover.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-plum flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-white">DI</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-1">Disability Insurance</h3>
              <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Replaces a portion of your income on an ongoing basis if you can't work. The longer benefit period (months to years) means your bills get paid even through extended recovery.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-4" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Getting the balance right</h2>
        <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p>The right combination depends on your life stage, income, dependents, existing coverage through work, and budget. A 35-year-old with a young family and a mortgage has very different needs from a 55-year-old approaching retirement with an empty nest.</p>
          <p>We review your full picture — including any group coverage you already have — and help you fill the gaps without over-insuring or duplicating coverage unnecessarily.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">Insurance products are offered through Heidi Blondin Financial / Qualified Financial Services. This article is for general information purposes only and does not constitute personalized insurance advice. Please consult with a qualified advisor to determine what coverage is appropriate for your situation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Build a complete protection plan" sub="Book a free consultation and we'll map out the coverage combination that actually covers you." />

</BaseLayout>
